verses.text: And Samson went down to Timnath , and saw a woman in Timnath of the daughters of the Philistines.
And he came up , and told his father and his mother , and said , I have seen a woman in Timnath of the daughters of the Philistines : now therefore get her for me to wife.

Then his father and his mother said unto him, \add Is there\add* never a woman among the daughters of thy brethren , or among all my people , that thou goest to take a wife of the uncircumcised Philistines ? And Samson said unto his father , Get her for me; for she pleaseth me well.\f + \fr 14.3 \ft pleaseth…: Heb. is right in mine eyes\f*

But his father and his mother knew not that it \add was\add* of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, that he sought an occasion against the Philistines : for at that time the Philistines had dominion over Israel. \p

¶ Then went Samson down , and his father and his mother , to Timnath , and came to the vineyards of Timnath : and, behold, a young lion roared against him.\f + \fr 14.5 \ft against…: Heb. in meeting him\f*

And the Spirit of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* came mightily upon him, and he rent him as he would have rent a kid , and \add he had\add* nothing in his hand : but he told not his father or his mother what he had done.
And he went down , and talked with the woman ; and she pleased Samson well. \p
¶ And after a time he returned to take her, and he turned aside to see the carcase of the lion : and, behold, \add there was\add* a swarm of bees and honey in the carcase of the lion.

And he took thereof in his hands , and went on eating , and came to his father and mother , and he gave them, and they did eat : but he told not them that he had taken the honey out of the carcase of the lion. \p
¶ So his father went down unto the woman : and Samson made there a feast ; for so used the young men to do.
And it came to pass, when they saw him, that they brought thirty companions to be with him. \p

¶ And Samson said unto them, I will now put forth a riddle unto you: if ye can certainly declare it me within the seven days of the feast , and find \add it\add* out , then I will give you thirty sheets and thirty change of garments :\f + \fr 14.12 \ft sheets: or, shirts\f*

But if ye cannot declare \add it\add* me, then shall ye give me thirty sheets and thirty change of garments. And they said unto him, Put forth thy riddle , that we may hear it.\f + \fr 14.13 \ft sheets: or, shirts\f*
And he said unto them, Out of the eater came forth meat , and out of the strong came forth sweetness. And they could not in three days expound the riddle.

And it came to pass on the seventh day , that they said unto Samson’s wife , Entice thy husband , that he may declare unto us the riddle , lest we burn thee and thy father’s house with fire : have ye called us to take that we have ? \add is it\add* not \add so\add*?\f + \fr 14.15 \ft take…: Heb. possess us, or, impoverish us?\f*

And Samson’s wife wept before him, and said , Thou dost but hate me, and lovest me not: thou hast put forth a riddle unto the children of my people , and hast not told \add it\add* me. And he said unto her, Behold, I have not told \add it\add* my father nor my mother , and shall I tell \add it\add* thee?

And she wept before him the seven days , while their feast lasted : and it came to pass on the seventh day , that he told her, because she lay sore upon him: and she told the riddle to the children of her people.\f + \fr 14.17 \ft the seven…: or, the rest of the seven days\f*

And the men of the city said unto him on the seventh day before the sun went down , What \add is\add* sweeter than honey ? and what \add is\add* stronger than a lion ? And he said unto them, If ye had not plowed with my heifer , ye had not found out my riddle. \p

¶ And the Spirit of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* came upon him, and he went down to Ashkelon , and slew thirty men of them, and took their spoil , and gave change of garments unto them which expounded the riddle. And his anger was kindled , and he went up to his father’s house.\f + \fr 14.19 \ft spoil: or, apparel\f*
But Samson’s wife was \add given\add* to his companion , whom he had used as his friend.
